tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE HousingConditions ( 
    id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    address STRING, 
    city STRING, 
    state STRING, 
    zipcode INT, 
    condition_rating INT, 
    affordability_rating INT, 
    available_units INT, 
    total_units INT 
)

CREATE TABLE HousingConditions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    address VARCHAR(255),
    city VARCHAR(100),
    state VARCHAR(50),
    zipcode VARCHAR(10),
    rent DECIMAL(10, 2),
    condition TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE AffordableHousingSolutions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name VARCHAR(100),
    target_population VARCHAR(100),
    budget DECIMAL(15, 2),
    implementation_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE HousingConditions (
    house_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    house_type VARCHAR(255),
    location VARCHAR(255),
    condition VARCHAR(255),
    cost DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE HousingDemographics (
    house_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    family_size INT,
    income DECIMAL,
    age_group VARCHAR(100),
    occupancy_status VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE HousingConditions (
    housing_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    address VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    state VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    zip_code VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
    condition VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE HouseholdMembers (
    member_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    housing_id INT REFERENCES HousingConditions(housing_id),
    name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT NOT NULL,
    occupation VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE HousingCosts (
    cost_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    housing_id INT REFERENCES HousingConditions(housing_id),
    monthly_rent DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    utilities_cost DECIMAL(8, 2),
    property_tax DECIMAL(8, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE HousingConditions (
    housing_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    address VARCHAR(255),
    city VARCHAR(100),
    state VARCHAR(50),
    zip_code VARCHAR(10),
    condition VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE HouseholdMembers (
    member_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    housing_id INT,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    occupation VARCHAR(50)
);
